clean_description: this ones for you new grads  the best cities to start your career have been ranked by wallethub using over two dozen metrics ranging from job growth rate and starting salary averages to average commute and housing affordability the best cities for starting a career not only have a lot of job opportunities but also provide substantial income growth potential and satisfying work conditions wallethub analyst chip lupo said its also important to consider factors such as how fun a city is to live in or how good of a place it is for raising a family to ensure life satisfaction outside of your career the release of the report comes as graduation season is in full swing  a time when many people are figuring out where in the country they want to kick off their professional lives the five cities that wallethub found to be most favorable for beginning a career were located in three different states the cities of charleston south carolina richmond virginia salt lake city utah columbia south carolina and pittsburgh pennsylvania are ranked no  through  respectively of the  locales included in wallethubs report the ones with the lowest overall scores for beginning a career were detroit michigan new york new york oxnard california bridgeport connecticut and pearl city hawaii   getty ap kevin ruck  stockadobecom

author: simply_sand
clean_description: ive been seeing more and more people start weight loss meds literally weeks after giving birth and honestly it breaks my heart a little because somewhere along the way we started believing that our bodies need to snap back immediately after bringing a whole human into the world like theres something wrong with taking time to heal like softness stretch marks or a bigger size means failure and i get it the pressure is everywhere social media floods us with bounce back culture before and after photos moms who lost the baby weight in a month and youre sitting there in mesh underwear leaking from everywhere wondering whats wrong with you but let me say this loud you dont need ozempic you just had a baby you need rest nourishment patience compassion you need time to feel like you again and that has nothing to do with a scale your body isnt behind its not broken its healing adjusting protecting you and taking care of your baby  even if it doesnt look like it used to and that is more than enough so if youre feeling like youre the only one not rushing to lose weight  youre not youre human youre healing and youre doing amazing tiktokhypemoms simplysand postpartumjourney postpartumbody
